htmlPage:
Mobile Moola Wallet

Description

This is an easy to open account that allows you to make and receive payments on the go. Your wallet is just a click away and you can access it immediately after applying for it.

What you can do

  • Make mobile-based payments
  • Make a limited number of payments on the go
  • Transfer money with zero monthly charges
  • Use facial recognition to make changes on your wallet (pin reset, unlock your account, etc)

What you need

  • Create an electronic profile on our app.

Instant Account

Description

The Instant Account is a simple no-service fee account. It is customized for a ‘load & go’ experience and anyone can be an Instant Account card holder. It is Zimswitch enabled and is linked FBC Bank’s Mobile Moola (*220#) and Mobile App.

What you can do

  • Simply and quickly register
  • Swipe and withdraw
  • Make instant transfers (ZIPIT)
  • Link your account to your mobile wallet of choice
  • Transact with zero monthly service fees
  • Transact with a zero minimum balance

What you need

  • National ID
  • Initial transfer of ZWL$20.00

htmlPage:
Current Account

Description

This is a transactional account for you. It allows you to enjoy 24/7 access to banking services through channels such as the FBC Mobile App, Mobile Moola (*220#) and Internet Banking.

What you can do

  • Cash withdrawals on FBC and ZimSwitch – enabled ATMs,
  • Purchase of local goods and services on Point Of Sale (POS) machines,
  • Mobile transfer to other banks,
  • Cash deposit,
  • Bill Payments,
  • Internal Transfer to FBC accounts,
  • Mini Statement,
  • Balance Enquiry linked to mobile wallets (Ecocash, Telecash and OneMoney),
  • Beneficiary / Receiver Management

What you need

  • National ID or valid passport
  • Proof of residence in your name (current)
  • Initial transfer of ZWL $50.00
  • Self-taken photo
  • Payslip or Confirmation letter from your employer

shortDescription: The FBC Savings Account is an interest-earning account designed to assist customers to securely grow their savings in a digital account in which balances are not affected by charges. The account can be opened within 5 minutes without the need to visit a physical branch. Minimum balance $100 Only one withdrawal are allowed per month No monthly service fees if savings are maintained within set criteria
productTerms: You will also need to note that there would be additional charges on this account on a monthly basis, the account will go dormant if it does not transact in 3monhts and may be closed if it does not transact within four months to manage costs of maintaining the account
productConditions: Attractive interest rates Interest accrues on the monthly minimum balance and  paid to customer account at the end of every month  No monthly service fees if savings are maintained within set criteria Additional deposits can be done anytime

shortDescription: Anyone who is interested in opening a foreign currency account can open an FBC Nostro FCA Account with FBC Bank. Funds held in a Nostro FCA account will be held as foreign currency in the currency in which the account is operated. Individuals are allowed to withdraw forex and make payments using their Nostro FCA accounts.  The Nostro FCA account will be opened immediately. Account will be opened within 5 minutes.
productTerms: USD Cash Deposits  USD Cash Withdrawals  USD Transfers Bill Payments in Foreign Currency Account Enquiries
productConditions: The FBC Nostro/FCA allows you to exclusively deposit and withdraw foreign currency from any of our branches.
fullDescription: The FBC Nostro/FCA allows you to exclusively deposit and withdraw foreign currency from any of our branches.
productMinimumRequirements: Copy of National I.D Proof of Residence Passport Size Photos Initial deposit of USD 30.00

FCA Account

Description

The FBC Nostro/FCA allows you to exclusively deposit and withdraw foreign currency from any of our branches.

What you can do

  • USD cash deposits
  • USD cash withdrawals
  • USD Transfers
  • Bill Payments in Foreign Currency
  • Account Enquiries

What you need

  • National ID
  • Proof of residence
  • Self-taken photo
  • Initial deposit of US$30

shortDescription: The ordinary mortgage loan is designed to assist customers to access loans for purchase or construction of residential or commercial property. The product has the following features: Product tenor varies with age to retirement (65 years) with a cap of 20 years, 12% interest rate 25% deposit Mortgage Establishment fees 1.5%, Valuation fees 1% Security- First mortgage bond IFO FBC Building Society Traceable proof of income Available to clients in Zimbabwe and Zimbabweans living abroad Clients to open a Homesave account with the Society
productTerms: You will also need to note that there would be additional charges on this account on a monthly basis, the account will go dormant if it does not transact in 3monhts and may be closed if it does not transact within four months to manage costs of maintaining the account
productConditions: A Card may optionally be created on this account, it will have a custom name on it, you have the liberty to choose a name that would be printed on your card, the default be Firstname SecondName initial. Surname
productMinimumRequirements: You need to have fully completed your profile, (Make sure a current proof of residence is uploaded, your selfie and valid ID Document are uploaded, employment information may also ensure that your account is done more quickly as well)

shortDescription: These are our personal loans to salaried individual borrowers. This product is for FBC Bank / Building Society account holders and walk-in clients. Unless additional security is provided, our maximum loan limit is \$5,000 with the sole requirement that loan repayments be within 40% of a borrower’s net salary. Call us now for a real quick loan.
productTerms: This product is exclusively for civil servants and carries the same pre-qualification conditions as our salary based loans. We cater for pre-existing FBC Bank/ FBC Building Society account holders or walk-in clients. However, in the case of civil servants, deductions are made via SSB stop orders. Government pensioner’s personal loans also require repayments within 40% of net pension. Our minimum loan amount is $100 with a maximum of up to $5,000. We cater for FBC Bank and Non FBC Bank Customers. Deductions are also via Government stop order facility.
productConditions: A Card may optionally be created on this account, it will have a custom name on it, you have the liberty to choose a name that would be printed on your card, the default be Firstname SecondName initial. Surname
productMinimumRequirements: You need to have fully completed your profile, (Make sure a current proof of residence is uploaded, your selfie and valid ID Document are uploaded, employment information may also ensure that your account is done more quickly as well)
